content.detailedDescription: I have been watching the skies recently due noticing flashes of white or blue light,like camrra flash,so i stood at my back door that night and noticed what looked like a larger star moving towards my house from a southern possition,then change direction and altitude heading north easterly,it climbed and stopped,then decended and stopped,climed and moved north easterly again.I felt it was aware of what i was doing and felt intimedated by it.It dissapeared over the houses and out of my sight.From then  i have had numerous sightings on more or less alternate days for a while and also captured more photos of those objects,i used the flash on one occasion and the sphere object stopped and changed colour,from white to red at which i am sure i was noticed by it.I have alot more photos of these encounters also.
content.summary: First looked like a larger star then started moving across the sky silently so grabbed my phone also had repeated sightings within days,weeks.

content.detailedDescription: Observed several craft in the sky at 9pm on 9/12/2015 going from nw to se. when i took a picture of them i was able to get three objects in the frame. when i enlarged the pic the setting sun in the west belite the objects which showed there shape. i have worked around aircraft for 30 years an it was a shape that i have never seen before.I was at work at the beginning of my shift.I noticed the bright lights moving across the sky making no noise that i could hear.They moved in a straight line about 2000 ft in the air an about 2000 to 3000 ft from me heading from nw to se with 1 bright orangish white light on each craft.I pulled out my phone an took apic an i was very amazed to see the outline of the crafts that i took.They traveled at the same speed an level until they left my eye sight.
content.summary: Three circles connected from top to bottom each smaller than above

content.detailedDescription:
1989 sighting location was in the dresser ranch tract  13 mi.E of paso robles ca, it hovered in our pasture momentarily until rocket was launched. my japanese wife and dog were in a dazed for several days after their encounter. 
i called vandenburg duty officer informing them of my suspicion, they said it was their launching of rocket, i argued the distance was to far from our ranch to the rocket site.& their next launch looked like a matchstick, this burning orange object was the size of a helo. he recommended calling lemoore naval air base because they were doing experimental flights, so once again i called 

a few days later insurance man shows ups claiming one of us called for an estimate, my wife tells him about the encounter but neither of us called? shortly afterwards we were awaken by bright search light lighting up the bedroom & our curtains were closed too there was no sound just a light rain i saw nothing and found no tire tracks at all that am on dirt circle driveway

also a another rancher nearby was having so many upsetting encounters she call cnn news and had a video to prove her story of harassment by ufo's to family & horses and called lemmore naval air base to complain many times.

its my opinion they were observing the launches and disguised their presences
by taking off exactly the same time as vandenburg launches its rockets.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change
content.summary: Ufo was waiting for vandenberg launch and left in sync with rocket launch

content.detailedDescription:
It was about 9:54 am i was driving along rt 53n in weymouth, ma when i was about to turn left into the friendlys restaurant parking lot when i saw a flashing light. i thought it was a plane but it was what appeared to be doing was reflecting  the sunlight from the east and it seemed to descend a bit and then it leveled off. the object was traveling south along rt 53 and i was stopped at  the entrance for about a minute to observe it. i then quickly  parked and turned my camera on to view it about 1 minute after i got out of car. . i was only able to record about 1.5 min of video because i was out of storage limit. i then observed it for about a half hour as it seemed to hover and shine like a star and move in a westerly directipn. i saw the same object saturday in south boston and recorded it as well as report it last night to mufon. 
i felt pretty excited. i was able to see it for about a half hour when it seemed to be too far away to keep my eyes  fixed on it. 
look at the center of the screen in video to see the object hover and flash lights or what i saw with sunglassed eyes was that it was reflecting the sunlight.
content.summary: I saw some flashing light as i was about to turn left into parking lot.

content.detailedDescription:
It was in the 70's,i'm guessing of the exact date and time, i was bush hogging on the farm at 1340 shinbone rd, lafayette, ga. it was after midnight we mowed after dark in the cool part of the day, i was riding an m farmall which is very loud when all a once i heard a buzzing sound. a craft came out of the woods from behind a ridge and a bright light hit me square in the face.

it surprised me, i mashed the clutch and brake because i could not see, it took several minutes for me to regain my composure and be able to once again see to operate the tractor.

by the time i was able to see the object was out of sight.

could it have been a plane? i can not say, the only light i recall is the light that hit me in the face.

i have been wondering about this incident since it occurred.
content.summary: Blinding light hit face & a buzzing sound.

content.detailedDescription:
I had been attending a baptism at a church. came out of the church with two others whom i was taking home in my car.  i turned around to see if they were following and saw this large object in the sky. i exclaimed "look" and the three of us stood and looked up.  i said immediately that it was a ufo, since i have seen them many many times before, over teesside airport.  the other witnesses are mormon and do not believe in such things as ufo.  


three of us saw what we thought at first were aircraft lights, since we are on a flight path from and to teesside airport. except that the large ball of light was a bright reddish orange.  it was irregular in shape, sort of round but not if you see what i mean.
no sound at all, total silence.  to the east of shafto way, newton aycliffe

it seemed to be moving as an aircraft would, then stopped and hovered, moving ever so slightly. after a few minutes it went higher and higher then disappeared, we thought behind a cloud.  nb have estimated the size against a boeing 737 usually seen in the sky at the same height and it was easily 7 or more times the size of an aircraft in the sky.

a minute or two later it reappeared slightly south of the first sighting, moved a short way then again hovered for a couple of minutes. it remained there for some time.   then simply disappeared behind a cloud. we stood and watched for a while longer but it had gone.
  

it was an amazing sight to see.  aircraft do not hover and this definitely hovered and appeared to be pulsating. we stood and watched the whole episode.

i have always known that there are beings on other planets, beings that visit the earth on a regular basis so was not totally surprised by what i had seen.

i posted this on a ufo uk website the same night, hence the details here. darlington is 7 miles south of newton aycliffe.  someone posted under my message the following -


october 12, 2012 at 9:25 am
hi 
i live in darlington and saw something similar over the weekend, but cannot recall which night.
i used to think that most sightings of orange lights were lanterns, but there have been a lot of credible sightings recently that are obviously not lanterns.
returning to what i saw, it was a large orange light which was visible to the east and was moving in a southerly direction. it was not flickering and did not gradually dim as lanterns do. i saw it for several minutes until it moved out of sight, perhaps behind a cloud.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Witnesses of ufo

content.detailedDescription:
Four of us were out on the deck observing the unobstructed night sky; there was no light pollution, so the stars were clearly visible for a few miles in either direction. we were looking toward the southeast, over the mid-coastline of maine. a friend and i spotted a red blinking light that we first thought was a distant plane. when it appeared to be changing direction, going back and forth at lightning speed, we called the others attention to it. after a few minutes the object did not move from view, and it began making 45 degree angle turns, and then returning to its original position. it continued with these maneuvers for approximately ten minutes before suddenly disappearing and not returning elsewhere in the sky. i am not terribly good at judging distances, but i feel comfortable in saying that this object was at least two or three miles away, which would place it over the atlantic ocean; it's height must have been at least 4-5,000 feet above sea level. even at these distances, it remained clearly visible for the duration, so i expect it was rather large.

i have always been interested in the subject of ufo's and have done considerable research on them for years. this is the first time in my long life of actually seeing one beyond any doubt in my mind.I have to admit i was thrilled to the point of being giddy with excitement. cross one off my bucket list!
content.summary: Red light with rapid changes in direction over atlantic coastline

content.detailedDescription: My friend was visiting from another city.  we were sitting in the hot tub at approximately 1am eastern time.  to the south-east i noticed a fast moving orange light travelling from south to the north.  i said to my friend "hey look at that" and pointed.  he saw it as well.  the object was in a group of 3, followed by a group of at approximately 10 more behind it.  the first object in the group of 3 may have been slightly brighter than the others as it was what drew my attention to them. upon seeing the first group of objects (3) it crossed my mind that they were meteors, but upon seeing the second group and the structured movement it appeared to be something else occurring. the objects were relatively low, much lower than jet aircraft typically fly, completely silent and extremely fast.  they didn't leave a trail, were yellow-orange in colour and their shape wasn't apparent. my feeling/impression of the event was that of surprise.  it was unlike anything i've seen before. we lost sight of the objects when our view was obscured by my house.
content.summary: A formation of over 10 yellow-orange lights flying from south to north, low, silent and fast.

content.detailedDescription: I was on my way to work at 9:50 pm maybe 50 feet from my house when i took a moment to stargaze something i do every night. as i looked towards the western skyline my vision instantly focused on the object. i stood amazed by the sight as i held back the urge to run inside with the intent to scream out loud that a u.F.O. was passing by in the sky over the next town over. instead i made a visual scan of the skyline and as luck would have it a commercial airliner was also flying nearby thus allowing me to get a size estimate. the object appeared to be half the size of the airliner despite appearing to be farther away. the object was an oval shaped light that slowly faded in and out of view as if a child was playing with a dimmer switch. the light also seemed to flicker after a couple of pulses. this pattern never changed. the airliner was heading toward the south east likely on its way to one of the airports out near boston can't say for certain.What i can say with certainty is that the object was traveling no less than twice the speed of the airliner as it traversed the sky. this was truly a life changing event as many members of my family have had encounters as well. i was excited to be able to add my name the list of family members with encounter tales.Lost sight of the object as it started getting too far away to tell it apart from the light pollution coming from the city of pittsfield.
content.summary: Saw orange- yellow oval shaped light in sky heading north from the south

content.detailedDescription:
On the evening of aug 19, 2015 i was driving west on mcdowell rd from my scottsdale apartment on my way to pick up my brother from work. the frist time i saw the objects its was 10:15pm. i was coming over a hill which over looks the whole south- south west side of phoenix. i saw two very bright orbs hovering near the red radio towers on south mountain south of phoenix. they were around 8 or 9 miles away and they were large. i continued on mcdowell rd to pick up my brother from work. around 10:35 on our way back the two orbs was now just one and it was at the same altitude as it was 20 minutes earlier but now on the east side of the radio towers. my brother took a brief video of the orb but we were on the side of a dark busy road and didn't feel safe standing on the side. we live near an air port and an army base so we see air craft take off and land every day and night, including the military helicopters. the orbs were not moving very fast but the were moving from west to east. there was very little cloud cover and we were able to see pretty far. i have seen small orange orbs before in phoenix but nothing like this. they were extremely bright for how far they were. then after we took the video the last visible orb just disappeared, almost faded away. the video is not the greatest quality because it was from a cell phone and it was pretty far away. in the video in the backround you are looking at phoenix below, and the red towers in the back. to the left of the red towers is the orb. also to our left is papago park mountain that is not visible but just to give you an idea. we were facing south-south west. the address above is roughly were we were standing and this address is roughly were we say the objects.   

*our location - 5579-5831 e mcdowell rd, phoenix, az 85008

*the objects location - south mountain village, phoenix, az
content.summary: Very bright orange orb seen over phoenix arizona. a very bright large pair of orange orbs hovering over just north of south mountian roughly 9 miles away

content.detailedDescription:
I am retired, 68 years old and have been getting up at least once during every night for the last six to eight years to use the bathroom.  my routine seems to be one or more trips around midnight to 1 am, 3 am or 5 am to do this, then go to the kitchen for a short drink of water, looking out my window to the east. therefore, i know what to expect to see out that window, in different weather conditions and time of year. 
last night at about 3:30 am i was amazed and perplexed to see a light (which i assumed was a star at first look) at least the brightness of venus in summer (much brighter than any stars in that direction - and in the opposite direction of venus' position), and oddly mis-shaped (like 2 stars of the same size and character overlapping about 40%, perfectly vertically... visualize a  number 8 where nearly half of the top circle has fallen into the bottom circle.)  while i watched it for nearly 40 minutes before going back to bed, it did not move, but its brightness would periodically dim slightly as if from cloud cover. i moved to several different rooms to hopefully get a better view and then went outside onto my patio for the best possible observation and to attempt to get a few pictures with my cell phone. to make the outdoor trip, i needed to deactivate our alarm system, which woke my wife who also came out to take a look for 5-10 minutes. she confirmed it was quite odd in its brightness, shape and location to be a star, but i must admit that her celestial knowledge baseline is much less than mine. my rational head is thinking it must certainly have been a star, but my gut and my analysis of the observation is that the data doesn't add up. i've never seen anything like it or even similar to it in that direction before. although there are some clouds tonight (sep. 16, its past midnight now), as we look into the eastern sky we can see some dim stars and airplanes flying over lake michigan along their usual flight paths... but there is no "standout light" in the location or region of sky that could possibly be whatever we saw last night. 
i took some photos, but they are junk, not worth sending. if desired, i could provide a sketch or more specific details. the sighting was nearly perfectly east of us and appeared to be quite far away in both distance and altitude, that's why i selected indiana as the location vs illinois.
content.summary: I saw/watched a very bright "star-like" non-moving light that was just slightly oblong, vertically, like 2 spheres slightly offset.

content.detailedDescription: Tonight while standing on the west facing porch of my country house on a clear moonless summer night, i noticed a bright aspirin sized cherry-red light moving from south-west towards the north about 2 inches above the tree-line.  i went inside to get the binoculars, but lost it as it went behind a large tree nearby when i returned.  thought it was a plane, but then i realized the navigation light should have been green (starboard wing), not red (port wing). i also didn't see any other colored or flashing lights like a normal night flying plane has.  i'd have assumed it to be an rc drone if it weren't for its apparently large size (5-20 ft) and high speed which seemed to be between 150 - 200 mph and with a complete absence of noise (approx. 3 miles away).  i'm pretty sure it wasn't a plane,  so could it have been a high performance drone or an et craft?   wish i knew.  my feelings at first were excitement, but now frustration has set in because i didn't get a picture of it. will keep my camera handy from now on...
content.summary: Large bright cherry red constant light moving from left to right 2 inches (apparent) above tree line

content.detailedDescription: I was outside by the community pool with three other people. we were just enjoying the afternoon. i looked up to watch clouds and noticed two white perfect circles way up in the sky. they were so far away that i could not distinguish the size of them. at first i thought they were balloons just floating in the sky, but then i noticed they were moving and darting around the nearest cloud to them.  i pointed them out to my friends and only one of them could see them (the others did not have their glasses or contacts with them).  we both agreed they were not balloons as they appeared to be playing hide and seek in the clouds.  it was very strange and i felt very excited to be witnessing such an event. i got the impression they did not think they would be noticed so high up and that they matched the cloud color (which were perfect white bulbous clouds).  they did not effect the clouds though, another odd trait i thought because they moved through them and yet i did not see holes or anything like that within the clouds they were moving through and around.  this went on for quite some time and i had to turn away as my neck was starting to hurt from looking up for so long.  my friends lost interest much sooner than i did and i would check up periodically to see if they were still there and eventually lost track of them.  i did try and take a picture and video of them, but they were so far away and matched the cloud color so well that my phone camera could not distinguish anything but the clouds.
content.summary: I saw two ufos flying in and out of the clouds. they were just zipping around, up, down, sideways.

content.detailedDescription: I have seen a few shooting stars before, but this light seemed to be staking out a area. we would still see it when no planes were in the area. whenever a plane would fly in the area it was in it would speed up,slow down chase, change altitude until plane was out of area. did repeatedly. like it had to reset to patrol position. it did not fly all over the sky. stayed in the same area. i got my daughter to come outside to verify what i was seeing. she saw the light,orb flying faster than the planes but keeping its distance. then just disappeared after 40 min. i tried to take photos and video. but had a  hard time getting settings for night time with its light so dim. will review later.
content.summary: Object appeared to track planes that flew  in its area of flight. witnessed over 15  planes it observed, tracked .

content.detailedDescription:
I was in south boston at a local park/playground on a swing laying on my back rocking back and forth when i noticed a flicker of light in the sky in the direction of where planes were in the sky above flying along a flight lane and my first thought was that it was from a plane but owing to the sunglasses i had on which give such a clear view i saw no plane just a litte object in the sw along the flight path moving but much higher than it and as it was moving about it was reflecting the sun light from the sun which was in the east behind a garage. so as this object moved about staying generally in the sw direction  it was reflecting the sunlight at me and i could see it clearly in the clouds. i tried to record it on my phone but i dont think i got anything plus it was too small. also, i lost sight about two minutes after i saw it but then observed it about few minutes later although this time it was stationary and starlike in appearance in the sense that it was bright like a star yet stars dont shine in the day time atleast we cant see one. this was odd. it wasnt the first time i had seen this starlike object in the sky during the day. also, that day i was able to point it out to another man who was equally baffled at what he observed. he said that it was unusual shining like a star in the day.  i was pretty fixated on object for a couple of  times. the first about 5-10 then i lost a visual about 5 min later i was looking up and saw it again this time about  about 15 min and the witness saw it as well. i did not get his name. i lost sight of object. i think because it was too small and far away to stay focused for long and when i did turn away and look again it was hard to find it for i was a bit tired from looking. 
i feel pretty awestruck.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change
content.summary: Sighting in boston.Ma looking southwest. late morning.

content.detailedDescription: I was driving along york/durham rd coming from stouffville, ontario to whitby.  i noticed  this red object in the sky to my right.  at first i didn't believe it was a ufo because i've never heard of a red one but it didn't look like any airplane that i'd seen either and i couldn't understand why it was red.  i couldn't really identify a shape as it was surrounded by this red glow but it was huge and was approaching as if to land as it was now flying low.  i tried to keep sight of it but since i was driving and it was very dark, i had to keep glancing at the road ahead.  finally i liost sight of it when trees got in the way.  it never passed over my vehicle so it must have landed.  i really kept a close lookout at the sky because i wanted to observe it.
content.summary: Driving on road and spotted glowing red object making descent.

content.detailedDescription: Observed object in the sky roughly around late june to early july while letting out our dogs. noticed a multicolored star-like object in the sky to the north west of us. believed it to be a star or space station but noted that it was to low for a star and the station was not near our location at first sighting. because we live out in the country with the nearest bright city being 25 miles away from us we knew that it was not lights from the city. it would disappear for a few days then reappear  and stick around for two to three days before disappearing again, this pattern has been constant for the past couple of months. we lose sight of it normally in the morning when the sun comes up.
content.summary: Star-like object in the sky stationary but observed pattern of staying two to three days then disappearing for three before returning to same area

content.detailedDescription:
I was awake at 5:15 a.M:
looking out of my bedroom window, i saw a bright light moving very fast,from left to right,blinking slowly.

i first thought- a airplane.

but then,it stopped instantaneously and dived instantly out of my field of vision. no noise,absolutely quiet. no fireflies-the weather was chilly (unusual for tallahassee this time of year)

i was unable to go to sleep,pondering the event.

at 5 45 a.M., i observed a bright light,moving from left to right- but this time further to the left in my field of vision. it stopped,after 4- 5 seconds of movement (horizontal), and dived quickly out if my field of vision.
i felt thrilled,thinking that i was experiencing something very significant.

i still  do.

would like to meet like- minded folks to discuss these things.

charles
content.summary: Bright light,changing direction instantaneously,moving fast

content.detailedDescription: Sept.15 2015. observed a stationary object which appeared to be around 4000 ft in the air with lights that constantly rotated in a green red blue yellow white pattern and never changed during observation. checked against google sky and active radar with nothing being close to the same area. after 20 min. the anomaly began to descend out if sight. this is the second time we have witnessed this object in the same area last time being approx. 4 months ago and followed same path.
content.summary: Hovering obfect nw of my location stationary for approx. 20 min then decended out of sight.

content.detailedDescription:
I was in my car, stopped at a stop sign, and noticed an object in the sky with bright lights in it's windows. i turned the corner to get a better look at the craft.  the color of the craft was a dark grey or black.  the thing that struck me odd was that there was no sound that i could detect.  after several minutes, the craft began to move away very slowly, still no sound.  i followed the craft down he road and out and into the country.  then, suddenly the lights went out and i could not see the craft.  i became scared and headed for home as quickly as possible.  when i walked into the house, my wife noticed that i was visibly shaking.  

my brother was a high ranking officer at wright patterson air force base in dayton.  i called him immediately and reported to him what i had seen.  

the following morning, i was driving to work.  i had a columbus radio station on, and they were talking about the ufo activity that had gone on the prior night.  

i told several people about what i had seen, and their responses were to laugh at me.  so, i never told anyone else.
content.summary: Seen hovering over houses close to my home.  stopped car and observed for several minutes.

content.detailedDescription: In the early morning of july 15, 2014 (not sure of the exact date) my dog barked to go outside. it was approximately 2:00 am. it was a clear night with a great display of stars overhead.  i went out with my dog to look at the sky as she did her thing.  as i looked northeast i observed what appeared to be a dim star that was moving to the south.  at once i felt that i was looking at a satellite as i have seen many pass over our area at night and this was moving at the right pace and had the right brightness.  as i watched it for about a minute i realized that there was a second satellite behind it about 4 degrees moving at the same speed and on the same line.  this seemed very unusual and something i had never observed before.  less than half a minute after i spotted the second satellite the first satellite suddenly grew in brightness and size until it had expanded to about 10 times it's original size and than just disappeared.  the second satellite continued as it had been for about another 5 seconds and than just faded from view.  i was amazed, and have given a great deal of thought to what i had seen.  the most realistic explanation is an enemy killer satellite shot down another and the government is keeping it under wraps.  but, that explanation does not consider how the second craft seemed to depart into deeper space nor the fact that an explosion in space might be hard to hide if done with conventional arms. perhaps it was aliens at war, i don't know what it was but it was bazar and very unnerving.
content.summary: Appeared that a satellite shot down another satellite.

content.detailedDescription: I was in karlsruhe, nd attending a bonfire when i was looking at the stars. i was looking up cause i had already seen a few shooting stars but one stuck out to me. i thought it was a shooting star when i seen it bolting accross the sky. but the object left a long yellow trail that vanished on its end to the middle in an almost syfy movie twist as if the object entered warp speed. i was shocked and alerted my friends that were around me and they were in awe as well. i lost sight of the object when it all of a sudden vanished into the darkness of the sky as if turning off a light switch.
content.summary: A shooting star like object

content.detailedDescription: The strangeness starting occurring while i was sleeping i had the most strange vivid dreams an then awoke at 5 am fully rested but with aches and pains all over my body ,  i usually sleep till 12 ish , at around 12 a black fighter jet looking aircraft zoomed over my town my girlfriend saw it at her house on the other side of town an my neighbors outside were all talking about it , let's skip to around 430 pm my girlfriends at my house she's giving me a back massage she's freaks out because she saw a weird diamond formation of red dots on my back she took a few pictures on her phone then we obviously joked saying i got abducted me being an avid ancient alien theorist i for a little seriously thought it could've been , so we look up on medical page after medical page we find nothing but people asking questions about it no answers i found one person who wrote a long article who supposedly compiled a number of cases an said that there was very few people who had pain but a large number if not all who had the strange dreams , i'm a little scared now thinking i have some rare skin disease or was abducted , so i go to my sisters house 5 or 6 miles away from my house i hung out for a few hours i'm now leaving i realize i forgot my phone i turn around as i'm coming through the neighborhoods an for some reason me an my girlfriend looked up at the same time an i felt somewhere in me that just said look up an we saw a blueish white fireball falling very fast it definitely wasn't flying , it had to have been at least 10 to 15 miles away but i have no idea if any of these experiences are correlated , but me an my girlfriend both confirmed we saw the same thing , an i'm not gonna lie we were so scared we were out loud saying that we would never talk about this but being as my body still feels odd i really need some answers it's not right that one sentient species can hold that kind of dominance over another please contact me by phone i never check my emails if you have any kind of explanation for all this or even just the dots
content.summary: Blueish white fire ball falling

content.detailedDescription: I've been watching the skies since 6/18/15 because ive been seeing things up there. on 6/22/15 i noticed something again in the sky. so i went and got my camera and started taking pics.It was about 10pm. the first one i noticed, it was yellow and orange and it looked like a hockey stick then it changed, then it looked like a big yellow flashlight then it changed again then it looked like a blue saucer then it changed again but whatever it changed to i couldn't tell u, i watched it off and on for about 4hrs and also took pics

content.detailedDescription: My boyfriend and i were driving down i.680 on september, 14th 2015 at about 11 pm, we had just passed the 84 exit to avoid going through livermore. sitting in the passenger seat i noticed bright lights, red, blue and lots of white. i leaned forward and started to observe it for a quick second noticing the craft was 3d like and triangular in shape. the white lights outlined the shape of the craft, knowing ive never seen anything like that and it was nothing near similar to a plane in shape or size i 2nd guessed myself and started to lean back. i took a quick glance at my boyfriend and realized he was looking at the same thing, i quickly looked back and within seconds the object blinked about 3 times (pulsating) when i thought the lights were going to blink again it vanished! we both looked at each other in shock, it was unreal. he was scared to drive underneath not knowing whether it had just cloaked and was still there. the whole time it was still above the freeway in perfect view, no movement at all. (we came home and i drew a sketch i couldn't make out every detail of the object but i remember white lights outline the bottom of the craft, panel like shutters if you want to call them on the side. very hard to describe,  i've never seen anything like it. it's like paper over lapping paper.)
content.summary: The object was enormous in size, dark triangular shaped 3d like unexplainable and unbelievable!

content.detailedDescription: Sometime around 11:30pm, i was approaching the main exits to albany from i-787. the road takes a distinctive curve there. as i drove out of the curve, the sky was noticeably lighter, almost like dusk, perhaps because of the lights around albany. i noticed what appeared to be a commercial aircraft way off in the distant sky. then much lower in the sky, a triangle of blue-ish lights entered my field of vision and descended at about a 45 degree angle at cartoonishly fast speed until the bridges and land along the interstate blocked my view. i wondered if it was a meteor, which i've seen before, but there was no trail behind it, there were three lights, it was not arcing, and it traveled at a very sharp angle. i have never seen any aircraft or object in the sky move at this rate of speed. it was incomprehensibly fast.
content.summary: Approaching albany on i-787, i saw three blue-ish lights in a triangle pattern zip down through sky at a 45 degree angle. unfathomable rate of speed.

content.detailedDescription:
After football practice on tuesday, october 18, 2011, i was talking with my d-line coach and my rb coach about our team while we stood at my truck, which was facing west.

during the conversation the rb coach just interrupted and said, "what is that?" both the d-line coach and i turned to look behind us and we seen a triangular shape object going from north to south, maybe south by southwest. it was triangular, but the edges seems smooth, or rounded, the exterior seemed at once silver/metallic, but also reflective kind of like water as the reflection was kind of wavy. however, it had a number of bright white circular lights around the edge, but not around the back of it and they seemed kind of large. the whole thing seemed large. i'm telling you it was definitely longer than from home to 1st base, but maybe not longer than a football field (100 yards). it was definitely between 500 feet and greater in the sky because it seemed like it was a couple of football fields off the ground. as we watched it, i noticed that the neighborhood dogs and birds were not making any noises as per normal, especially the dog that was always barking at us during and after practices in the yard of the house right on the border of the park. then out of nowhere it just disappeared. i didn't see it go anywhere. it was just gone.

both my asst. coaches and i were kind of stunned i think because we were all quiet looking at the area it disappeared from. then we looked at each other and began to ask again what that was. the d-line coach said, "well it wasn't birds." my rb coach said, "maybe it was a military ship." now, not too long before that there was a military plane/historical plane show somewhere to the west of northglenn because during a game we had parents, and even my players, oohing and ahhing the planes, i remember a stealth bomber was there (loud enough to hear from where we were) and what they were doing. i said, "yeah, probably a military plane of some kind."

but, for some reason this night and that object have bothered me ever since. i'm not sure why. i almost think i'm losing my dang mind because it will pop into my head out of nowhere and i just don't want to think about it anymore. i want it to go away.

i hope someone there can tell me a rational, logical explanation of what the heck we seen. my d-line coach is a born-again christian, iirc, and my rb coach is a catholic-christian like me. i don't buy into this little green men thing. or i didn't. or i still don't. i don't know anymore. all i know is i hope by telling you this you will have someone come ask questions i can't think to ask and show me that what we seen has a rational/logical explanation. i know what i seen. i see it clear as day. not only am i a coach, well, retired coach due to medical issues making it impossible to be an effective coach, but i'm also an artist. so, details sort of stick in my mind for the most part because of being a coach and an artist. so, i know what i seen was real... how could all 3 of us have seen something, the same thing!, and it not be real. i just want someone to help me understand what the heck we seen and why it bothers me so dang much so it will stop bothering me.

i read you have lots of reports and i understand you're busy. but, please consider helping me understand this. i would greatly, greatly appreciate it.

thank you,
coach.
content.summary: After football practice while i was talking w/2 of my asst. coaches about the team, one of my coaches noticed something behind us and asked what is that. other coach and i turned and watched it move silently to the south.
